text: The Cathedral of Santa María () is a cathedral in Calahorra, Spain. The building is protected for its historic interest and has been since 1931. In Spanish it is called a Bien de Interés Cultural (property of cultural interest). == References == ==Other websites== *Virtual Tour of the Cathedral of Santa María Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:La Rioja Category:15th-century buildings and structures
